Sec. 55.003. ARTICLES OF INCORPORATION. In addition to the
requirements prescribed by the general corporation laws of the state,
the articles of incorporation of an association formed under this
chapter must state that the association may not obtain loans for,
make loans to, purchase notes from, or discount notes for a person
who is not a member of the association.
Acts 1981, 67th Leg., p. 1122, ch. 388, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 1981.

